Global Copper-clad Aluminium Wire Market Insights
Copper-clad Aluminium Wire Market size was valued at USD 1.2 Billion in 2022 and is projected to reach USD 2.0 Billion by 2030, growing at a CAGR of 7.3% from 2024 to 2030.

Copper-clad Aluminium Wire Market Overview
The global Copper-clad Aluminium (CCA) Wire market size was valued at USD 9.0 billion in 2023 and is expected to grow at a CAGR of 5.5% from 2023 to 2030. This growth is driven by increasing demand for energy-efficient materials and the rising adoption of CCA wire in telecommunications, electrical applications, and renewable energy sectors. Copper-clad aluminium wires are preferred due to their low weight, corrosion resistance, and cost-effectiveness compared to pure copper wires. These wires are widely used in various applications like electric power distribution, automotive, and communication systems.

